Default Input View jQuery Plugin v0.5
-----------------------------
Copyright (c) 2011 Justin McGuire. Licensed under the MIT License.
Contact: mcguire.justin@gmail.com

Overview
--------

Fill in a text input with a default value, that disappears when you click on it
to fill in a real value.

Special Features:
    - If the user actually types in the default value, we'll still recognize it
      as user input, and it won't be automatically deleted on the next click.
    - The default text *won't* be submitted with the form.


Example Usage
-------------

HTML:

    Date: <input type="text" class="date" />

Javascript:

    $('input.date').defaultInputValue({
        default_text: 'MM/DD/YYYY',
    });

CSS (optional, but recommended):

    .no_value { color: gray }


Parameters
----------

default_text

 - Required, this is the default value of the text field.

no_value_class

 - This is the CSS class that will be applied to the input element when it is 
   filled with the default text. It defaults to 'no_value'.


Misc Notes
----------

Minimum jQuery versions:

